Loly

Target IP: 192.168.194.121

Scanning


There is only one TCP port open on the taget machine: HTTP.

Enumeration

Port 80: HTTP

The default webpage of nginx! is displayed when I visit this port.


Doing a directory search against this host only shows one result: /wordpress. When using a browser to access this WordPress application, the hostname loly.lc is shown. I used the vim and appended the line 192.168.194.121 loly.lc inside the /etc/hosts file. Now I can connect to the host!


The WordPress webpage above is displayed when I browse to /wordpress directory. Navigating around the website, I noticed a user called loly. Maybe I can perform a password against this user?


Since xmlrpc is enabled on the target machine, I used the following command wpscan --password-attack xmlrpc -U "loly" -t 20 -P /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt --url http://loly.lc/wordpress to launch a password attack against loly. And I obtained this user's password, which is fernando.

Exploitation


I now have access to the WordPress application as the user loly. Spraying the credentials loly:fernando worked. Time to gain a foothold on the machine now.


There is an interesting plugin installed called AdRotate. This plugin allows file upload. Maybe I can use this feature to upload a shell on the target machine? It allows certain types of files including zip.


I created a file called shell.php that has PHP Pentest Monkey reverse shell script. After, I zipped the content for the file upload and saved it as shell.php.zip.



Then I uploaded the shell.php.zip file and it says it is successful! This plugin settings all banner contents are saved under /var/www/html/wordpress/wp-content/banners/.


Therefore, I should be able to access my reverse shell script at http://loly.lc/wordpress/wp-content/banners/shell.php. I fired up a listener on port 8443 and visited the shell location, and obtained a reverse shell connection! Now I have a foothold on the machine as www-data.

Privilege Escalation



The wp-config.php contains the username and password above. Maybe I can spray this password lolyisabeautifulgirl against the user loly. And it worked. I am now the user loly.



The kernel version is interesting. Doing a Google search shows it is vulnerable to a local privilege escalation exploit as shown above.


Time to run this exploit. I transferred the exploit to the target machine and ran it as loly to gain a root shell.

Flags
